ALLEN Thompson, president of the National Teachers’ Union, has died. Natu spokeswoman, Nthabiseng Malusi , broke the news through social media. “It’s true, our president has departed,” Malusi confirmed to Daily Sun yesterday. She declined to comment any further as she was still to meet with the family for more details. KZN education spokesman, Muzi Mahlambi, said they were saddened by Thompson’s death. “The department has suffered a great loss. Thompson was like a big tree of knowledge. The role he played in the department was huge,” he said. He said Thompson would forever be missed for his contribution within the department. The contribution ensured that the tasks of teaching and learning went smoothly.